'''Bulgebi''' is a nearly extinct [[Finisterre languages]] of [[Papua New Guinea]]. It is spoken in the [[Madang Province|Madang]] province near the [[Astrolabe Bay]] and the lower [[Nakina River|Nankina]] river, slightly inland on the eastern end of the southern coast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.language-archives.org/language/bmp|title=OLAC resources in and about the Bulgebi language|website=www.language-archives.org|access-date=2017-02-10}}</ref>
