{{Notability|Organizations|date=March 2011}} {{Infobox Organization |name = Film Music Guild |image = |image_border = |size = <!-- default 200 --> |alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> |caption = |map = <!-- optional --> |msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 200px --> |malt = <!-- map alt text --> |mcaption = <!-- optional --> |abbreviation = FMG |motto = |formation = |extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> |type = <!-- GO, NGO, IGO, INGO, etc --> |status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> |purpose = <!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> |headquarters = |location = [[La Mirada, CA]] |coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> |region_served = |membership = |language = <!-- official languages --> |leader_title = <!-- position title for the leader of the org --> |leader_name = <!-- name of leader --> |main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> |parent_organization = [[Biola University]] |affiliations = <!-- if any --> |num_staff = |num_volunteers = |budget = |website = http://www.filmmusicguild.com |remarks = }}
The '''Film Music Guild''' (FMG) is a student organization at [[Biola University]] in [[La Mirada, CA]]. The Film Music Guild was formed to teach film students about music and music students about film.
==History== The Film Music Guild was formed in 2006 by composition student [[Dave Martina]] to fill the gap between [[Biola University|Biola]]'s music and film departments.<ref>http://www.biola.edu/100percent/instrumental/</ref>
==The FMG Conference== On October 3, 2009, the Film Music Guild hosted the first annual Film Music Guild Conference (called the FMG Conference 2009). Speakers included [[Pete Docter]] (director, ''[[Up (2009 film)|Up]]'', ''[[Monsters, Inc.]]''), [[John Ottman]] (editor and composer, ''[[Valkyrie (film)|Valkyrie]]'', ''[[Superman Returns]]'', ''[[X2 (film)|X2: X-Men United]]''), [[Christopher Young]] (composer, ''[[Spider-Man 3]]'', ''[[The Grudge]]'', ''[[Ghost Rider (2007 film)|Ghost Rider]]''), and many others.<ref>http://mixonline.com/news/fmg_2009_conference_0608/</ref>
